## Falsification Criteria
- If normalized owner earnings trend turns negative for 2+ years, bullish conclusion is falsified.
- If required return proxy (WACC) rises above sensitivity grid max, valuation confidence is invalid.
- If terminal growth assumption exceeds long-run nominal GDP proxy, conclusion is invalid.
